- What?
- That's impossible.

84
00:04:01,558 --> 00:04:02,540
Bail was five million.

85
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:04,454
That's probably nothing to her.

86
00:04:04,478 --> 00:04:06,305
I heard she billed Medicare
over $20 million a year

87
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:07,529
for unnecessary chemo.

88
00:04:07,564 --> 00:04:09,531
But her accounts were frozen.

89
00:04:09,566 --> 00:04:11,450
She found the money somewhere.

90
00:04:11,485 --> 00:04:13,546
That won't change the
outcome. She's a murderer.

91
00:04:13,570 --> 00:04:14,736
The jury will convict her.

92
00:04:18,942 --> 00:04:21,309
We have interviews at the clinic

93
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:23,945
for our new primary care doc.

94
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,964
- Yeah.
- Good, I'll meet you there.

95
00:04:25,999 --> 00:04:28,200
I have to check
in with Dr. Austin.

96
00:04:31,204 --> 00:04:32,637
I can't believe this.

97
00:04:32,673 --> 00:04:35,807
We have to let the
legal system do its job.

98
00:04:42,983 --> 00:04:46,918
I'm thinking two zolpidem
and a half a quart of whiskey.

99
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:49,438
He left a fine woman
at the altar last night

100
