101
00:04:51,224 --> 00:04:52,941
I have no sympathy.

102
00:04:52,976 --> 00:04:55,327
Go home!

103
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:57,412
- Ooh.
- I can't.

104
00:04:57,447 --> 00:05:01,116
Priya's there. She doesn't leave
for San Francisco until Friday.

105
00:05:01,151 --> 00:05:03,535
Wow, no wife and no home.

106
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:05,770
I at least feel pity for you.

107
00:05:05,806 --> 00:05:07,633
He was sniffing around
Julian. The device rep?

108
00:05:07,657 --> 00:05:10,825
An engaged man out
there, on the prowl.

109
00:05:13,163 --> 00:05:15,797
I thought better of you.

110
00:05:19,586 --> 00:05:21,536
You're a little too hard on him.

111
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,971
The heart wants
what the heart wants.

112
00:05:24,007 --> 00:05:26,374
Sometimes the
head has no control.

113
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,826
We all have a moral compass,

114
00:05:27,861 --> 00:05:29,872
and we have a choice
to follow it or not.

115
00:05:29,896 --> 00:05:32,124
He had feelings for Julian?
He should have avoided her.

116
00:05:32,148 --> 00:05:33,543
Instead, he kept
spending time with her.

117
00:05:33,567 --> 00:05:35,316
What did he think would happen?

118
00:05:35,351 --> 00:05:38,653
Anyway, when I'm done
with the clinic, I'll find you.

119
00:05:38,688 --> 00:05:40,304
What do we have on deck?

120
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,974
Uh, just a VATS case.

121
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:46,361
You'll be bored.
Go join Dr. Voss.

122
00:05:52,619 --> 00:05:53,896
<i>Here are files</i>

123
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,069
on the candidates.

124
00:05:55,105 --> 00:05:57,589
Are you going to be
volunteering on a regular basis?

125
00:05:57,624 --> 00:06:00,258
Bai was our first med
student to sign up.

126
00:06:00,293 --> 00:06:01,988
Who do we have first?

127
00:06:02,012 --> 00:06:04,379
Um, Dr. Christina Ruiz.

128
00:06:04,414 --> 00:06:07,398
Graduated from Johns
Hopkins in family medicine.

129
00:06:07,433 --> 00:06:09,250
Huh, sounds promising.

130
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:10,835
Let's get started.

131
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:12,114
<i>Your clinic would
be the perfect fit</i>

132
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:13,371
for me.

133
00:06:13,406 --> 00:06:14,900
I spent last year in Haiti
with Partners in Health.

134
00:06:14,924 --> 00:06:16,919
I grew up in Atlanta
and want to give back.

135
00:06:16,943 --> 00:06:18,660
Serve the underserved.

136
00:06:18,695 --> 00:06:20,540
Access. Too many
hospitals treat and street.

137
00:06:20,564 --> 00:06:22,531
There's no continuity.

138
00:06:22,566 --> 00:06:24,583
Do you have any
questions for us?

139
00:06:24,618 --> 00:06:27,368
Yes. The salary posted,
was that monthly?

140
00:06:27,403 --> 00:06:28,903
I'm kind of between jobs.

141
00:06:28,938 --> 00:06:30,366
What if you pay my
malpractice insurance?

142
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,706
I've got a fair number

143
00:06:31,741 --> 00:06:33,592
of totally frivolous lawsuits.

144
00:06:33,627 --> 00:06:35,127
I'm sorry, but with the amount

145
00:06:35,162 --> 00:06:37,012
of med school debt I'm carrying,

146
00:06:37,047 --> 00:06:38,975
you don't need a
physician, you need a saint.

147
00:06:38,999 --> 00:06:40,849
Is that really everyone?

148
00:06:40,884 --> 00:06:42,901
Okay, uh, I wasn't
gonna mention it,

149
00:06:42,936 --> 00:06:44,919
because it's a super long shot,

150
00:06:44,954 --> 00:06:49,057
but if "saint" is the
criteria, I do know of a guy.

151
00:06:52,629 --> 00:06:54,646
Oh, there he is.

152
00:06:54,681 --> 00:06:56,764
Dr. Alec Shaw.

153
00:06:56,799 --> 00:07:00,569
First he was an
infectious disease doc,

154
00:07:00,604 --> 00:07:03,971
then he volunteered on a
Navajo reservation doing outreach.

155
00:07:04,007 --> 00:07:06,541
After that he got
into family medicine.

156
00:07:06,576 --> 00:07:08,943
I first saw him in my
hometown, New Orleans.

157
00:07:08,978 --> 00:07:10,556
Why didn't you
mention him before?

158
00:07:10,580 --> 00:07:12,497
He just landed in Atlanta.

159
00:07:12,532 --> 00:07:14,049
He's always on the move.

160
00:07:14,084 --> 00:07:16,251
And he hates hospitals.

161
00:07:16,286 --> 00:07:18,403
Hates institutionalized
medicine.

162
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,088
Oh. I like him already.

163
00:07:20,123 --> 00:07:23,341
So he has no fixed
practice? No office?

164
00:07:23,376 --> 00:07:26,728
He has kind of an office.

165
00:07:26,763 --> 00:07:29,431
Well, let's go talk to him.

166
00:07:29,466 --> 00:07:32,434
Um, you'll have
to wait your turn.

167
00:07:32,469 --> 00:07:35,436
He never lets
anyone jump the line.

168
00:07:35,471 --> 00:07:37,366
Hmm. My shift
starts in 20 minutes.

169
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:39,440
Oh, you guys go. I-I got this.

170
00:07:39,493 --> 00:07:40,670
- You sure?
- Yeah.

171
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:41,910
All right, good luck.

172
00:07:50,654 --> 00:07:52,454
- Thank you, Doctor.
- You bet.

173
