top, courtesy of QuoVadis.

176
00:08:01,081 --> 00:08:02,942
You're now the device
rep? Where's Julian?

177
00:08:02,966 --> 00:08:04,799
Who-who's Julian?

178
00:08:04,834 --> 00:08:06,801
Hold on.

179
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:10,722
I bet you're more
of a glazed man.

180
00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:13,875
H-How about jelly? No?

181
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:15,960
That guy is Julian's
replacement.

182
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:17,729
Where is she?

183
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,163
I don't know.

184
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:20,793
She said she was gonna
quit and leave town,

185
00:08:20,817 --> 00:08:22,317
and now she's ghosting me.

186
00:08:22,352 --> 00:08:23,951
That's harsh.

187
00:08:23,986 --> 00:08:26,070
Look, about yesterday,

188
00:08:26,105 --> 00:08:28,657
I'm sorry, man.

189
00:08:28,692 --> 00:08:31,158
How's your dad?

190
00:08:31,194 --> 00:08:33,295
Not clear yet.

191
00:08:33,330 --> 00:08:35,413
You should go home.

192
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:37,715
I don't have one at the moment.

193
00:08:37,751 --> 00:08:39,050
And I'd rather work.

194
00:08:39,085 --> 00:08:41,002
I hear that.

195
00:08:43,673 --> 00:08:45,390
There's an arm lac in ER Three.

196
00:08:45,425 --> 00:08:47,842
I think you might
want to take this one.

197
00:08:50,547 --> 00:08:52,375
- Okay.
- Look, what do you want me to do?

198
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,826
They're gonna stitch me
up and then we'll leave.

199
00:08:53,850 --> 00:08:55,861
I... you know, I didn't
mean to fall, I fell.

200
00:08:55,885 --> 00:08:57,347
We should have
just watched it on TV.

201
00:08:57,371 --> 00:08:59,521
No way. You, of all
people, had to be there.

202
00:08:59,556 --> 00:09:01,200
I'm Dr. Hawkins.
What's going on?

203
00:09:01,224 --> 00:09:04,058
We were at a
protest, it got crazy.

204
00:09:04,093 --> 00:09:06,528
- At the prison?
- Yeah.

205
00:09:06,563 --> 00:09:08,758
And neither one of us are
happy that we ended up here.

206
00:09:08,782 --> 00:09:10,702
Lane Hunter killed
Roger's sister.

207
00:09:10,734 --> 00:09:12,211
She came in with
stage I breast cancer.

208
00:09:12,235 --> 00:09:14,920
Lane treated it
like it was stage IV.

209
00:09:14,955 --> 00:09:17,755
All Judy probably
needed was a lumpectomy.

210
00:09:17,790 --> 00:09:21,343
Instead, she died from a
reaction to Dr. Hunter's chemo.

211
00:09:21,378 --> 00:09:23,627
I am so sorry.

212
00:09:23,663 --> 00:09:26,214
I am not exactly a fan
of Dr. Hunter either.

213
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,534
Let's have a look at that arm.

214
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,398
- She had a pretty bad fall.
- Uh, it was a big crowd.

215
00:09:32,422 --> 00:09:34,050
I tripped. Just stitch me
up and send me home.

216
00:09:34,074 --> 00:09:36,057
Natalie used to be a cop.

217
00:09:36,092 --> 00:09:38,738
- Nothing fazes her.
- Well, I'm seeing
some bruising here.

218
00:09:38,762 --> 00:09:40,973
I'm gonna order an X-ray just
to make sure there's no fracture.

219
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:42,313
Hey, you're not hearing me.

220
00:09:42,348 --> 00:09:45,400
I'm fine. Stitch me and I'm out.

221
00:09:45,435 --> 00:09:46,734
And she doesn't like doctors.

222
00:09:46,769 --> 00:09:49,553
I get it. I know
what Dr. Hunter did.

223
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:53,591
Dr. Hunter gave Natalie chemo
and she didn't even have cancer.

224
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:56,127
She's the reason
I'm no longer a cop.

225
00:09:58,782 --> 00:09:59,992
Soon as I get an
answer, I'll let you know.

226
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,016
Doc-Doctor Bell.

227
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,458
Yeah?

228
00:10:10,493 --> 00:10:12,010
My hero.

229
00:10:12,045 --> 00:10:13,979
Dr. Bell, you have a call...

230
00:10:15,348 --> 00:10:17,348
I bailed you out,

231
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:19,746
<i>I got you a great legal team.
Now it's time to hand over</i>

232
00:10:19,770 --> 00:10:21,302
the deposition and the tape.

233
00:10:21,337 --> 00:10:24,355
I'm checking into a
very nice hotel. Come by.

234
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,090
<i>Alone, of course.</i>

235
00:10:26,126 --> 00:10:27,609
And let's discuss.

236
00:10:27,644 --> 00:10:29,277
I'll send my lawyer.

237
00:10:29,312 --> 00:10:31,128
Excuse me. Turn around here,

238
00:10:31,164 --> 00:10:32,680
<i>go to Chastain Park.</i>

239
00:10:32,716 --> 00:10:35,000
I'm on my way to you.

240
00:10:36,736 --> 00:10:38,736
What hotel?

241
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:45,271
Roger and I became
friends at Dr. Hunter's clinic.

242
00:10:45,295 --> 00:10:47,323
Poor guy drove his sister to
every one of her appointments.

243
00:10:47,347 --> 00:10:48,963
That's a good brother.

244
00:10:48,998 --> 00:10:51,715
Yeah, that's what I tell him,
but he still blames himself.

245
00:10:51,751 --> 00:10:54,486
What diagnosis were you given
for the weakness in your legs?

246
00:10:54,521 --> 00:10:56,387
Neuropathy from the chemo.

247
00:10:56,423 --> 00:10:58,701
It just won't get better.
Yeah, today it's even worse.

248
00:10:58,725 --> 00:11:01,126
Protest must have
really wore me out.

249
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:03,122
Well, let's make
sure it's nothing more.

250
00:11:03,146 --> 00:11:04,907
-We have one of the best -No.

251
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:07,192
Orthopedic spinal surgeons
in the country, Dr. Voss.

252
00:11:07,216 --> 00:11:09,150
I want her to check you out.

253
00:11:09,185 --> 00:11:12,170
Look, I was a legacy
officer in the Atlanta PD.

254
00:11:12,205 --> 00:11:15,189
My mom before me,
Grandpa before that.

255
00:11:15,224 --> 00:11:17,892
I wish I could have
