just treated its first patient.

507
00:23:30,559 --> 00:23:32,621
Well, he still needs that
consult, so it looks like

508
00:23:32,645 --> 00:23:34,456
you're going to
Chastain after all.

509
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:37,064
Natalie definitely has
chemo-induced cardiomyopathy.

510
00:23:37,099 --> 00:23:38,782
And the compression fracture

511
00:23:38,818 --> 00:23:41,035
has a large bone
fragment that's causing

512
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:42,831
- her spinal cord compression.
Decompression and fusion

513
00:23:42,855 --> 00:23:44,487
is the only way to give her

514
00:23:44,523 --> 00:23:46,940
- a chance of walking.
- We need to get in there now.

515
00:23:46,976 --> 00:23:49,476
Implant the cage
here for spine fusion.

516
00:23:49,512 --> 00:23:51,223
Her heart might not
be strong enough.

517
00:23:51,247 --> 00:23:53,058
- She's in the ICU
on an amio drip.
- We can try

518
00:23:53,082 --> 00:23:54,448
to manage it with ACE inhibitors

519
00:23:54,483 --> 00:23:55,677
- and beta-blockers...
- We don't have time.

520
00:23:55,701 --> 00:23:57,345
We've got three,
maybe four hours

521
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:59,637
before the compression
becomes irreversible.

522
00:23:59,672 --> 00:24:01,255
<i>If</i> she survives surgery.

523
00:24:04,543 --> 00:24:07,845
Lane took Natalie's
choices away.

524
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:11,515
We're giving her this one back.

525
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:12,516
I came in for some
damn stitches!

526
00:24:12,551 --> 00:24:13,829
Natalie, they're trying to help.

527
00:24:13,853 --> 00:24:16,186
This is crap! My options are

528
00:24:16,221 --> 00:24:17,916
full paralysis or
possible death?

529
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:19,284
Or full recovery.
That's the hope.

530
00:24:19,308 --> 00:24:20,636
We do the fusion

531
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:22,420
while monitoring
your cardiac function.

532
00:24:22,444 --> 00:24:24,828
You're the heart guy, right?

533
00:24:24,864 --> 00:24:25,829
So?

534
00:24:25,865 --> 00:24:27,009
Well, under normal
circumstances,

535
00:24:27,033 --> 00:24:28,415
I would advise against it,

536
00:24:28,450 --> 00:24:31,351
but these are not
normal circumstances.

537
00:24:33,739 --> 00:24:34,839
Dr. Hawkins...

538
00:24:34,874 --> 00:24:36,874
what would you do?

539
00:24:42,214 --> 00:24:44,526
You are the one who's gonna
have to live with this decision,

540
00:24:44,550 --> 00:24:47,218
so you are the one
who needs to make it.

541
00:24:47,253 --> 00:24:50,387
But if it<i> was</i> me...

542
00:24:50,423 --> 00:24:53,974
I am not letting Lane
Hunter hold me down.

543
00:24:54,009 --> 00:24:56,510
I'm taking the risk.

544
00:24:58,764 --> 00:25:01,148
Crap.

545
00:25:03,319 --> 00:25:05,168
I got to try.

546
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:12,826
- You gave me a scare.
- They said...

547
00:25:12,861 --> 00:25:15,162
I almost died.

548
00:25:15,197 --> 00:25:17,281
I'm sorry I wasn't here.

549
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:20,334
I shouldn't have left you.

550
00:25:20,369 --> 00:25:23,721
Always taking the weight of
the world on your shoulders.

551
00:25:23,756 --> 00:25:25,806
The blame.

552
00:25:25,841 --> 00:25:28,425
Not this time.

553
00:25:28,460 --> 00:25:30,493
Well, you asked for
one thing: no Bell.

554
00:25:31,763 --> 00:25:33,647
I guess he's
better than nothing.

555
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:47,194
I want things to change for us.

556
00:25:47,229 --> 00:25:50,580
I've waited a long time
to hear those words.

557
00:25:50,616 --> 00:25:52,699
Well, hey, we're both stubborn.

558
00:25:52,735 --> 00:25:55,569
Yeah, that's... that's true.

559
00:25:58,957 --> 00:26:00,841
Hmm.

560
00:26:00,876 --> 00:26:04,428
I have spent half my
life without a father.

561
00:26:05,764 --> 00:26:07,932
We're gonna fix that.

562
00:26:07,967 --> 00:26:10,800
I'm gonna hold you to that.

563
00:26:25,768 --> 00:26:27,016
Thank you.

564
00:26:28,837 --> 00:26:32,039
Excuse me, um, I'm
looking for Dr. Bell's office.

565
00:26:32,074 --> 00:26:34,208
Tenth floor.

566
00:26:34,243 --> 00:26:36,460
Hey, uh, you're
Julian's boss, right?

567
00:26:36,495 --> 00:26:37,578
Yeah. Gordon Page.

568
00:26:37,613 --> 00:26:40,130
Devon Pravesh. Have you spoken

569
00:26:40,165 --> 00:26:42,327
- to Julian today?
- No. She didn't show up
for work.

570
00:26:42,351 --> 00:26:44,001
Had to get a replacement.

571
00:26:44,036 --> 00:26:46,098
A no-show isn't like
her, but I guess it's

572
00:26:46,122 --> 00:26:48,555
because of what she's
been going through.

573
00:26:48,590 --> 00:26:51,425
Yeah. She, um, mentioned
some issues with work.

574
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:53,643
Really? What'd she tell you?

575
00:26:54,847 --> 00:26:56,230
Honestly, not much.

576
00:26:56,265 --> 00:26:57,743
Yeah, Julian told
someone in the office

577
00:26:57,767 --> 00:26:59,967
that she got too close
to a doctor at Chastain,

578
00:27:00,019 --> 00:27:01,947
and it turned into
more than she wanted.

579
00:27:01,971 --> 00:27:04,521
I just hope he didn't
scare her off. She's good.

580
00:27:04,556 --> 00:27:06,506
Anyway, thanks
for the directions.

581
00:27:11,781 --> 00:27:13,157
Great news. Ophthalmology says

582
00:27:13,181 --> 00:27:15,126
that Russell's eye
is looking good.

583
00:27:15,150 --> 00:27:17,045
They're gonna keep him
overnight for observation.

584
00:27:17,069 --> 00:27:19,189
Is that necessary?
It's gonna rack up a bill

585
00:27:19,221 --> 00:27:20,715
- he won't be able to pay.
- Hey.

586
00:27:20,739 --> 00:27:22,283
- Can I help? I doubt
you can do anything

587
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:23,551
about a bloated
hospital billing system

588
00:27:23,575 --> 00:27:25,793
that charges 300
bucks for an aspirin.

589
00:27:25,828 --> 00:27:27,294
Conrad, this is Dr. Shaw.

590
00:27:27,329 --> 00:27:28,712
Alec, Dr. Hawkins.

591
00:27:28,747 --> 00:27:30,809
- We're trying to get him
to run the clinic.
- Ah.

592
00:27:30,833 --> 00:27:32,693
Can't get past the
toxic hospital culture,

593
00:27:32,717 --> 00:27:33,851
the lack of transparency,

594
00:27:33,886 --> 00:27:35,101
the endless documentation...

595
00:27:35,137 --> 00:27:36,720
Don't forget about the upcoding,

596
00:27:36,755 --> 00:27:38,667
fragmentation of care,
over-testing, overtreatment.

597
00:27:38,691 --> 00:27:40,952
- Not helping.
- Look, we know

598
00:27:40,976 --> 00:27:42,792
we're going up against Goliath.

599
00:27:42,828 --> 00:27:45,145
And it's true, all
we got's a slingshot.

600
00:27:45,180 --> 00:27:47,481
But we have damn good aim.

601
00:27:47,516 --> 00:27:50,200
Well, it seems like a
waste of both your talents.

602
00:27:50,235 --> 00:27:52,118
I do my own thing. Sorry.

603
00:27:52,154 --> 00:27:53,370
Eh. No worries.

604
00:27:53,405 --> 00:27:54,883
Just remember, wars are
fought on the battlefield,

605
00:27:54,907 --> 00:27:56,206
not from the sidelines.

606
00:27:56,241 --> 00:27:57,752
Look, let me buy
you a cup of coffee,

607
00:27:57,776 --> 00:27:59,471
- introduce you to the team...
- No, I got to get back.

608
00:27:59,495 --> 00:28:02,162
It's nice meeting you, Nic.

609
00:28:03,765 --> 00:28:06,500
Damn. He was perfect.

610
00:28:08,904 --> 00:28:11,104
I don't believe it.

611
00:28:24,070 --> 00:28:25,497
Deflating the lung.

612
00:28:27,956 --> 00:28:30,123
Dr. Voss, you
have spinal access.

613
00:28:31,443 --> 00:28:33,505
I would have risked
the surgery, too.

614
00:28:33,529 --> 00:28:35,112
Really? You would

615
00:28:35,147 --> 00:28:37,831
risk it all just for a chance
of something better?

616
00:28:37,866 --> 00:28:39,511
For the chance at
the life you want,

617
00:28:39,535 --> 00:28:41,034
so would I.

618
00:28:42,905 --> 00:28:44,132
Oh, hell.

619
00:28:44,156 --> 00:28:46,290
The bone is weak from the chemo.

620
00:28:46,325 --> 00:28:48,703
- I can't get fixation.
- What about a graft
from her hip?

621
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:50,294
We can't get it fast enough.

622
00:28:50,329 --> 00:28:52,629
Dr. Okafor, what's our move?

623
00:28:54,649 --> 00:28:56,550
Let me see her X-rays.

624
00:28:59,305 --> 00:29:00,787
All right, show me her ribs.

625
00:29:04,343 --> 00:29:07,027
They're less damaged. We
can make a graft from her ribs.

626
00:29:07,062 --> 00:29:09,396
How long do you think it'll
take? Her echo was showing

627
00:29:09,431 --> 00:29:10,959
severely depressed
ejection fraction.

628
00:29:10,983 --> 00:29:12,349
We'll have to move fast, then.

629
00:29:19,691 --> 00:29:21,258
Julian?

630
00:29:29,084 --> 00:29:30,834
Hey, it's Devon.

631
00:29:30,869 --> 00:29:32,502
Are you okay?

632
00:29:33,839 --> 00:29:35,789
Look, I know I
shouldn't be here,

633
00:29:35,824 --> 00:29:39,092
but, um, what you
said about QuoVadis...

634
00:29:39,128 --> 00:29:41,728
we should talk about it.

635
00:29:41,763 --> 00:29:43,947
We should talk about everything.

636
00:29:45,184 --> 00:29:46,583
Just call me.

637
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:48,434
Please.

638
00:29:59,198 --> 00:30:01,731
All right, he's gone.

639
00:30:02,734 --> 00:30:03,917
Mr. Page?

640
00:30:03,952 --> 00:30:05,919
Yeah, the place is clean.

641
00:30:05,954 --> 00:30:08,705
Someone came by.

642
00:30:08,740 --> 00:30:10,290
Yeah, same guy.

643
00:30:12,878 --> 00:30:14,711
Security's on the way.

644
00:30:14,746 --> 00:30:18,181
This office is a
shrine to your ego.

645
00:30:18,217 --> 00:30:20,684
Lacking confidence without me?

646
00:30:20,719 --> 00:30:22,330
Hardly. You have
about two minutes

647
00:30:22,354 --> 00:30:24,888
to say whatever it is
you came here to say.

648
00:30:24,924 --> 00:30:28,608
You know, words aren't
getting through to you, Randolph.

649
00:30:28,644 --> 00:30:32,362
So I thought that this... might.

650
00:30:36,268 --> 00:30:39,369
Really brings out the
desperation in your eyes,

651
00:30:39,404 --> 00:30:41,321
don't you think?

652
00:30:41,356 --> 00:30:43,540
Where did you get that?

653
00:30:43,575 --> 00:30:45,576
That lawyer you found me,

654
00:30:45,611 --> 00:30:47,393
he can dig up anything.

655
00:30:47,429 --> 00:30:49,796
Now, tell me something.
What do you think is worse?

656
00:30:49,832 --> 00:30:51,860
Trying to buy sex
from an undercover cop

657
00:30:51,884 --> 00:30:54,518
or failing to
self-report your arrest

658
00:30:54,553 --> 00:30:56,587
to the State Medical Board?

659
00:30:58,790 --> 00:31:00,907
So, where's the copier?

660
00:31:00,942 --> 00:31:02,893
I think everyone

661
00:31:02,928 --> 00:31:05,512
- will want their very own.
- You're a monster.

662
00:31:06,715 --> 00:31:08,698
Look around, Randolph.

663
00:31:08,734 --> 00:31:10,833
Either you agree
to tell the jury

664
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,853
how wrong you were about me,

665
00:31:12,888 --> 00:31:15,522
or all of this disappears.

666
00:31:15,557 --> 00:31:17,324
You can call off your dogs.

667
00:31:17,359 --> 00:31:19,860
Happy to show myself out.

668
00:31:22,814 --> 00:31:24,764
♪ ♪

669
00:31:31,540 --> 00:31:33,940
Nice of you to stop by.

670
00:31:35,961 --> 00:31:38,295
Sorry.

671
00:31:38,330 --> 00:31:40,129
Busy morning.

672
00:31:40,165 --> 00:31:42,048
You're recovering well.

673
00:31:42,101 --> 00:31:44,718
Hematocrit's stable.
Kidney function's good.

674
00:31:44,753 --> 00:31:46,397
I'm a little surprised
you didn't kill me

675
00:31:46,421 --> 00:31:47,888
when you had the chance.

676
00:31:50,258 --> 00:31:52,153
You know, my first
year as an attending,

677
00:31:52,177 --> 00:31:54,944
they brought a guy into
my OR with six bullet holes.

678
00:31:54,979 --> 00:31:56,708
He killed two cops,
and everybody said

679
00:31:56,732 --> 00:31:58,198
he deserved to die.

680
00:31:58,233 --> 00:32:00,383
When I pick up a
scalpel, I don't care

681
00:32:00,419 --> 00:32:01,868
who's on the other end.

682
00:32:01,904 --> 00:32:03,703
That's the discipline.

683
00:32:03,738 --> 00:32:06,405
I'm a surgeon first. That's
all that matters to me.

684
00:32:06,441 --> 00:32:09,076
Oh, so you wanted to
kill me, but you were...

685
00:32:09,111 --> 00:32:10,776
too principled.

686
00:32:10,829 --> 00:32:12,311
That's charming.

687
00:32:25,594 --> 00:32:26,977
<i>You</i> paged me?

688
00:32:27,012 --> 00:32:29,646
You don't 911-page
me to come to you.

689
00:32:29,681 --> 00:32:30,847
That's Natalie Ramirez.

690
00:32:30,882 --> 00:32:32,733
Lane Hunter ruined her life.

691
00:32:32,768 --> 00:32:35,185
Destroyed her
heart and her spine

692
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:36,464
with chemo that she didn't need.

693
00:32:36,488 --> 00:32:38,955
And now she may die in that OR.

694
00:32:39,941 --> 00:32:42,192
And she's one of the lucky ones.

695
00:32:42,227 --> 00:32:44,177
You think I don't care? I do.

696
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:47,163
Then why was
Lane in your office?

697
00:32:50,536 --> 00:32:52,869
Guess what. I am sick and tired

698
00:32:52,904 --> 00:32:55,955
of you thinking you have
any right to question me.

699
00:32:55,991 --> 00:32:56,957
You're a resident.

700
00:32:56,992 --> 00:32:58,759
Who I would love to fire.

701
00:32:58,794 --> 00:33:00,788
Except your father,
whose life I just saved...

702
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:02,012
Thank you very much...

703
00:33:02,047 --> 00:33:03,446
Would fire me.

704
00:33:03,481 --> 00:33:05,043
So you got me down
here to see this woman.

705
00:33:05,067 --> 00:33:07,017
I've seen her.

706
00:33:07,052 --> 00:33:08,052
Good for you.

707
00:33:08,086 --> 00:33:10,387
Made my day.

708
00:33:10,422 --> 00:33:11,866
If Lane gets off,
how many others

709
00:33:11,890 --> 00:33:14,023
like Natalie will there be?

710
00:33:28,106 --> 00:33:29,834
This should do the trick.

711
00:33:29,858 --> 00:33:30,840
Spinal nerves

712
00:33:30,875 --> 00:33:31,875
still viable.

713
00:33:35,264 --> 00:33:36,524
She's in V tach again.

714
00:33:36,548 --> 00:33:37,664
Wet laps.

715
00:33:37,699 --> 00:33:39,076
The anesthesia

716
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:40,762
is too much for her
heart. We need to stop.

717
00:33:40,786 --> 00:33:41,929
Get the cage and screws ready.

718
00:33:41,953 --> 00:33:43,898
- Clear.
- Just let me finish fusing.

719
00:33:43,922 --> 00:33:45,066
- Clear!
- It's in.

720
00:33:49,961 --> 00:33:52,078
On three. One, two, three.

721
00:33:52,114 --> 00:33:54,080
Clear.

722
00:33:56,468 --> 00:33:57,745
She needs double
sequential defibrillation.

723
00:33:57,769 --> 00:34:00,036
Give her another 150 amio.

724
00:34:00,072 --> 00:34:01,232
Start a procainamide drip.

725
00:34:04,943 --> 00:34:07,460
Clear. And go.

726
00:34:13,202 --> 00:34:16,435
She doesn't have the time
you need to finish the spine.

727
00:34:16,471 --> 00:34:18,733
We need to take her back
to the ICU, let her stabilize.

728
00:34:18,757 --> 00:34:20,040
We do that, she's paralyzed.

729
00:34:20,075 --> 00:34:21,591
We don't and she's dead.

730
00:34:21,626 --> 00:34:23,326
Can you stabilize her here?

731
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:26,974
Central line to assess
the cardiac index

732
00:34:26,998 --> 00:34:29,532
and output numbers. How
long would it take, Okafor?

733
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:30,611
For most, five
minutes. For you, four.

734
00:34:30,635 --> 00:34:32,130
And if she needs
ventricular assist?

735
00:34:32,154 --> 00:34:33,720
20 to deploy percutaneously.

736
00:34:33,755 --> 00:34:35,900
Her spine can stay in a
sterile dressing while you work.

737
00:34:35,924 --> 00:34:38,086
I need 30 to finish, then
we get her back to ICU.

738
00:34:38,110 --> 00:34:39,821
All right. Heart first,

739
00:34:39,845 --> 00:34:41,811
then spine, if
she's still stable.

740
00:34:41,846 --> 00:34:44,481
And if her spinal
cord is still viable.

741
00:34:56,328 --> 00:34:57,794
Nic?

742
00:34:57,829 --> 00:34:59,546
You're here.

743
00:34:59,581 --> 00:35:01,665
Grant applications.

744
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,416
All day...

745
00:35:03,451 --> 00:35:05,230
I've been trying to
get you to join us.

746
00:35:05,254 --> 00:35:06,630
And it has been...

747
00:35:06,654 --> 00:35:09,472
a day.

748
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:12,291
There's so much I can't fix.

749
00:35:12,327 --> 00:35:15,795
But this, this clinic...

750
00:35:15,831 --> 00:35:18,264
I can do.

751
00:35:18,299 --> 00:35:21,601
And I'll do it without you.

752
00:35:21,636 --> 00:35:23,103
Don't get me wrong...

753
00:35:23,138 --> 00:35:24,771
What you're doing here is great.

754
00:35:24,806 --> 00:35:27,774
But is it really
about the patients?

755
00:35:27,809 --> 00:35:29,809
Seems like...

756
00:35:29,862 --> 00:35:33,113
you'd rather rail
against a broken system

757
00:35:33,148 --> 00:35:34,792
than actually
fight to change it.

758
00:35:34,816 --> 00:35:36,365
You serious?

759
00:35:36,401 --> 00:35:38,785
I spent the better part
of my life in service.

760
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:40,286
All I do is fight.

761
00:35:40,322 --> 00:35:43,072
Well, maybe not hard enough.

762
00:35:49,548 --> 00:35:51,515
<i>So, this is about one</i>

763
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:53,127
- of your employees?
- Julian Booth.

764
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:56,519
Um... she never
showed up for work today

765
00:35:56,555 --> 00:35:59,055
and is not the type
to just disappear.

